  "doc_id": "61100",
  "text": "When Kerenidis and Prakash's work was published, their algorithm was exponentially faster than the best-known classical algorithms. It was not known whether this was a provably exponential speedup. The goal of this work is to describe a classical algorithm that performs the same task as the quantum recommendation systems algorithm with only polynomially slower runtime, thus answering this question. This removes one of the most convincing examples we have of exponential speedups for machine learning problems (see Section 6.7 of Preskill's survey for more context [CITATION_1] ).",
